Multi-asset Digital Investment Platform

At VentureCrowd, we have developed and created a vertically integrated, full service alternative asset platform and products business that can raise funds from investors for venture and property opportunities, develop complex property projects, provide fund administration and undertake marketing and sales activities. This vertical integration maximises revenue generation from all activities and ensures optimal service delivery to our investors. Our end-to-end digital investment platform offers purpose-driven alternative assets to retail and wholesale investors.

Our product mix includes debt, equity and hybrid securities with differing risk-reward profiles in property and venture capital – previously only available to wholesale investors.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Property

VentureCrowd has built a full-scale property team based in Brisbane Australia that includes architects, engineers, developers and development managers with the ability to originate and manage end-to-end property development projects internally, generating proprietary property deal-flow for the platform. VentureCrowd’s property arm is a targeted differentiation strategy that ensures proprietary deal flow in a highly attractive alternative asset class and has been successful in driving investor registration and capital raising volumes.

Our team has the capability to undertake all aspects of the development process, from land sourcing, through to obtaining approvals, managing construction and the sale of off-the-plan dwellings. Once a development opportunity has been secured, VentureCrowd packages each part of the capital stack for the project separately and offers the opportunity to invest in that financial product to our 67,000+ members. Typically, this includes: pure equity in the initial phase of a project, the preference equity and/or mezzanine debt during the civil construction phase, and first mortgage loans in the construction phases of a project.

Once a financial product offering is closed, each financial product is managed by our funds management team under the relevant licence. This vertically integrated model is unique to VentureCrowd and allows the business to have complete control over all aspects of the delivery of both the financial product and the underlying asset.

Our Industries in Focus

We provide access to a wide range of asset classes and with a key focus on high growth industry sectors, such as:

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Property

For investors, the coming years present a prime opportunity to secure substantial gains in the real estate market with no signs of slowing down. VentureCrowd is especially optimistic about regional property markets. Driven by affordability, lifestyle appeal, and work flexibility, regional property values have climbed an average of 15.2% (compared to 9.4% in major cities) over the past year. VentureCrowd raises funds for real estate development projects and participates in capital structures ranging from equity to mezzanine debt, depending on the project.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Foodtech

The Foodtech industry is booming. Despite challenges in 2020, Foodtech startups raised $26B, a 35% increase from 2019. Foodtech is projected to become a $346B market by 2027, growing at 6% annually.

Consumers want nutritious, sustainable, healthy food options, which legacy food companies haven't provided. Foodtech startups are seizing these opportunities. COVID-19 has accelerated these trends. Clearly, Foodtech is shaping the future of food.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Healthtech, Medtech & Biotech

Technology is poised to revolutionise healthcare and usher in a new era focused on health and wellness rather than just treatment. This consumer-centric approach is the future of healthcare innovation. The digital health market is projected to grow tremendously over the next decade, reaching USD$258 billion by 2028. This growth will be fuelled by demand for greater convenience, personalisation, and access to high-quality, affordable care.

Technology is empowering people to take control of their health and facilitating a shift to a preventive mindset. The digital health revolution is making healthcare tailored, effective, and safer than ever before. The future of healthcare is here, and it's putting people first.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue

Renewables

We passionately enable our community to invest in and improve our world. At VentureCrowd, we carefully select investment opportunities that benefit investors and the environment. In 2020, the impact investing market was valued at USD $715 billion in assets globally. Clearly, sustainability is a top priority for achieving financial returns. We aim to remain leaders in this area.

Our Market

As the digitisation of the global investment management sector moves into its most impactful phase yet and the core financial services customer profile shifts from baby boomers to the next generations, technology platforms are replacing legacy investment management organisations and many traditional financial services intermediaries will simply cease to exist.

Impact and purpose-driven investing will continue to rise as millennials and members of Gen Z become the beneficiaries of the largest intergenerational wealth transfer in history and redirect trillions of investment dollars into new, sustainable industries and projects.

Over the next few years, blockchain technology’s practical use cases in the wealthtech sector will achieve mass adoption and by the end of the decade, the transition to Web3 will have profoundly changed the industry.


Market Drivers

VentureCrowd has been at the forefront of the wealth sector’s digital transformation. Looking ahead, the sector is being driven by a number of material macroeconomic trends that are creating strong tailwinds for the business, including:

  • Digitisation and Web3
  • The growing popularity of alternative assets
  • The rise of millennial& Gen Z investors
  • Increasing focus onpurpose-driven investments
  • Lack of trust in traditional financial institutions

While the majority of traditional financial services organisations cautiously observe the impact of these macroeconomic trends, VentureCrowd has built its business in anticipation of them, uniquely positioning the business to advance its position as a leading next-generation digital investment brand.

Growth in Alternative Assets

Heightened volatility on listed equity markets and continued uncertainty regarding the outlook for defensive assets once considered ‘safe’ have contributed to the rising popularity of alternative assets among investors seeking higher rates of return.

In Asset & Wealth Management 2025, PwC forecasts there will be a boom in alternative asset popularity among Asian investors – especially Real Estate and Infrastructure investments – as alternative AuM grows from US$ 2.9 trillion in 2017 to US$ 6.9 trillion by 2025, a staggering CAGR of 11.7%.

According to Deloitte, “Investors are adjusting their portfolio allocations in search of total return. In the retail market, this adjustment includes an expanding eye toward alternative investments.”

With this trend likely to continue, VentureCrowd is well placed to grow its market share in Australia and Asia by offering quality alternative asset investment opportunities to retail, wholesale and institutional investors.

This vertical integration maximises revenue generation from our activities. Our end-to-end digital investment platform offers purpose-driven alternative assets to retail and wholesale investors. Our corporate structure, inclusive of entities facilitating our diverse range of operations, allows us to undertake a breadth of services for ventures, property, and funds opportunities.

The Fund

VentureCrowd Trust No. 0665 (VentureCrowd Services Australia) (Fund) is structured as an unregistered wholesale unit trust, the trustee of which is VentureCrowd Nominees Pty Ltd (ACN 166 599 140). Investors will acquire Units in the Fund at an issue price of $1.00 per Unit.

The Trustee will issue Units to investors in its capacity as an authorised representative of VentureCrowd Pty Ltd (ACN 166 598 849) under Australian Financial Services License No.503381.

The Fund will acquire preference shares in VentureCrowd Services Australia Pty Ltd (ACN 638 909 878), the entity that provides shared corporate services to the entities within the VentureCrowd Group.

Risks

Whilst the directors of VentureCrowd are experienced business managers with deep experience in the key areas that are core to the operation of this business, there are always risks associated with investing in venture capital opportunities which may, either directly or indirectly, result in reduced distributions and/or a loss of some of the capital value of an investment in the Fund. Before deciding whether to subscribe for Units, you should consider whether an investment in this Fund is suitable for you and obtain professional advice.
